The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Bhutias 1st for Perak
 BY A STAFF REPORTER  Bhaichung Calcutta, Aug. 30: Bhaichung Bhutia has opened scoring in Malaysia. The Indian star scored the first in Perak FCs 2-1 win over Malaka in Saturdays Malaysian Cup match. Bhutia, who was hospitalised after Wednesdays match with high fever, played the full match and scored in the first half. Perak took a 2-0 lead after the breather before conceding a late equaliser. I started feeling tired in the closing stages, but finished the match nonetheless, Bhutia told The Telegraph, while travelling to Ipoh (where Perak FC is based) from Malaka on Saturday. It was Bhutias third match in the Malaysian Cup. In this tournament, 16 teams are divided into four groups, with the top two from each proceeding to the quarter finals. The teams play each other twice in the group league, on home and away basis. Saturdays was Peraks away match at Malaka and they had won the home match 5-0 on Wednesday. Bhutia will be in Mumbai for a promotional programme on Sunday and return to Ipoh on Tuesday. Peraks next match is slated for Wednesday.  Copyright 
